    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.02576.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">
                        <handShift rend="printed"/> J<hi rend="smallcaps">ohn</hi> H. J<hi rend="smallcaps">ohnston</hi>. A<hi rend="smallcaps">lbert</hi> E<hi rend="smallcaps">dw</hi>. J<hi rend="smallcaps">ohnston</hi>. <lb/> J.
                        H. JOHNSTON &amp; CO., <lb/> Diamond Merchants and Jewelers. <lb/> 17 Union
                        Square, New York. <lb/> C<hi rend="smallcaps">or</hi>. B<hi rend="smallcaps">roadway</hi> &amp; 15<hi rend="smallcaps">th</hi> S<hi rend="smallcaps">t</hi>. <lb/>
                        <milestone unit="undeclared" rend="horbar-short-center"/>
                        <lb/> Established, 1844. <lb/> Telephone Call: 916 21st Street. </name>
                    <name type="place">New York,<ptr target="loc.02576_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1890-09-23"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Sept 23 <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>90</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt:</salute>   
            </opener> 
            <p>Your postal<ptr target="loc.02576_n2"/> is rec'd—I sent the material<ptr target="loc.02576_n3"/> you mailed me to Ingersoll,<ptr target="n0839"/> and
                have no doubt he will find it useful—</p>
            <p>Now then; If you can get to Phil for an even'g—What is to hinder your being
                wheeled into a car and being whisked over here in two hours, then after three days
                good solid rest, with Mrs Davis<ptr target="n6113"/> &amp; your nurse<ptr target="loc.07319_n6"/> to help, you will be able to go to one of our great
                Halls or Opera house &amp; listen to Ingersoll.<ptr target="loc.02574_n3"/></p>
            <p>In other words—If the thing comes off here, it will knock Phil. right
                out—I believe<pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.02576.002.jpg" type="verso"/>
                you can stand it easy—</p>
            <p>Alma<ptr target="n3029"/> says "We will give Uncle Walt our floor and he will be as
                comfortable as any one possibly can be"<ptr target="loc.02574_n4"/></p>
            <p>We live in Stuyvesant Square, 4 story wide house 3 rooms deep, so you see you can
               sling cats if you want to.</p>
            <p>Think this over, and lets see if we cannot teach the owners of your Academy a
                lesson.</p>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02576.003.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#unk">16.05</note>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#unk">W.H. Neidlinger</note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02576.004.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely Yours</salute>
                <signed>JH Johnston</signed>
            </closer>
        </body> 
